Reference implementation: jehangiramjad/tslib (Robust Synthetic Control)
========================================================================

This benchmark cross-validates mlsynth's PCR (principal component regression /
robust synthetic control) against the ORIGINAL Robust Synthetic Control:

    https://github.com/jehangiramjad/tslib
    Authors: Jehangir Amjad, Devavrat Shah, Dennis Shen
    Implements: Amjad, Shah & Shin, "Robust Synthetic Control",
                Journal of Machine Learning Research 19(22):1-51, 2018.

The class used is ``src/synthcontrol/syntheticControl.py::RobustSyntheticControl``
(the OG RSC: hard singular-value thresholding of the stacked donor+treated
pre-matrix, then an unconstrained pseudo-inverse / OLS of the de-noised treated
row on the de-noised donor rows -- no intercept, no simplex constraint).

The repository carries no LICENSE file. Rather than vendoring un-licensed source
into mlsynth, the reference is fetched on demand at a pinned commit and imported
from a local cache; nothing from it is redistributed in this tree.

Fetch (performed automatically by benchmarks/reference/clone_tslib.py):

